definitions.definition: A subfamily of the Semitic languages, which were spoken by the ancient peoples of the Canaan region, including Canaanites , Israelites and Phoenicians .

main_definition: A subfamily of the Semitic languages, which were spoken by the ancient peoples of the Canaan region, including Canaanites , Israelites and Phoenicians .

definitions.definition: A member of the ancient Semitic people who occupied Canaan before its conquest by Israelites .
A member of the Canaanism movement.
